# Cloudflare Pages redirects
#
# Pretty URLs (.html extension stripping) are handled automatically by
# Cloudflare Pages — no rules needed for that.
#
# What we DO need: collapse the four URL variants into one canonical
# (https://www.wabashsystems.com). Without these, Google indexes
# wabashsystems.com, www.wabashsystems.com, http://, and https:// as
# separate hosts and splits ranking authority across all four. The
# canonical <link> tag is a hint; a 301 is definitive.
#
# Cloudflare "Always Use HTTPS" (zone-level setting) handles http -> https
# at the edge before the request reaches Pages, but we list http sources
# here too as defense in depth (and so this works even if that toggle
# ever gets turned off).
#
# Both wabashsystems.com and www.wabashsystems.com are configured as
# custom domains on the Pages project, so requests to either reach this
# rules file. The :splat token captures whatever follows the wildcard.

http://wabashsystems.com/*       https://www.wabashsystems.com/:splat   301
https://wabashsystems.com/*      https://www.wabashsystems.com/:splat   301
http://www.wabashsystems.com/*   https://www.wabashsystems.com/:splat   301
